  Read every `.rs` under `src/`, the `Cargo.toml(.orig)`, the README, the
  changelog, and the CI config.
  
  Concern #1 (malicious): clean. No `build.rs`, no proc-macros in this
  crate (proc-macros live in the separate `bytemuck_derive` dep, gated
  by the `derive` feature). No network, no process spawning, no
  filesystem I/O, no `include_bytes!`, no obfuscation. Triple-licensed
  (Zlib/Apache-2.0/MIT). Well-known author Lokathor; this is the de
  facto safe-transmute crate in the ecosystem. The 1.25 delta is small:
  drop `extern "stdcall"` fn-ptr impls on non-x86-32 Windows (PR 333)
  and unblock `nightly_portable_simd` after libcore's `LaneCount`
  removal (PR 344) — both straightforward fixes. An opt-in
  `unsound_ptr_pod_impl` feature exists, is documented as unsound, and
  is excluded from the docs.rs/playground feature sets.
  
  Concern #2 (`unsafe` without SAFETY): inconsistent. `src/transparent.rs`,
  `BoxBytes`, and `TransparentWrapperAlloc` carry good `// SAFETY:` lines.
  But many `unsafe { ... }` blocks in `src/internal.rs`, `src/must.rs`,
  `src/checked.rs`, `src/allocation.rs` (e.g. `try_zeroed_box`,
  `try_cast_box`, `try_cast_vec`, `try_cast_slice_box`) lack explicit
  `// SAFETY:` comments. In context the invariants are usually obvious
  (size/align just checked, or the enclosing `unsafe fn` carries the
  contract), but per the rubric this caps rating at `neutral`.
  
  Concern #3 (miri): CI (`.github/workflows/rust.yml`) runs
  `cargo miri test --no-default-features` and `cargo miri test
  --all-features` on the crate, plus `-Zsanitizer=address` and
  `-Zsanitizer=memory` builds. Solid validation of the unsafe surface.
  No additional cap.
  
  Concern #4 (correctness): no bugs found. The size/align gating in
  `internal::try_cast*` and `allocation::try_cast_{box,vec,slice_*}`
  is consistent (handles ZSTs explicitly, checks `input_bytes %
  size_of::<B>()`, treats `Layout` size+align as the dealloc contract,
  uses `ManuallyDrop` to defuse the donor `Vec`). `BoxBytes` preserves
  its alignment-layout invariant on drop.
