comment: |-
  Read every .rs file under src/ (lib.rs, io.rs), Cargo.toml(.orig), README.md,
  CHANGELOG.md, and .github/workflows/ci.yml. No build.rs, no proc-macros, no
  runtime deps (dev-deps: quickcheck, rand). No network/filesystem/process I/O
  beyond the documented Read/Write extension traits. License: Unlicense OR MIT.
  Author is BurntSushi (Andrew Gallant), longstanding ecosystem maintainer.
  
  Concern #1 (malicious): none found.
  
  Concern #2 (unsafe w/o SAFETY): the crate contains ~30 `unsafe` blocks across
  lib.rs and io.rs. None carry the conventional `// SAFETY:` comment. The
  bodies are idiomatic: (a) `slice::from_raw_parts_mut(_ as *mut U, len)` to
  reinterpret &mut[i{16,32,64,128}]/&mut[f{32,64}] as their same-size unsigned
  counterpart — sound because size_of and align_of match (lib.rs:1091, 1120,
  1149, 1178, 1208, 1270, etc.; an `align_of` const-assert is even present at
  lib.rs:1209/1271); (b) `slice_to_u8_mut` (io.rs:1587) reinterprets &mut[T:Copy]
  as &mut[u8] — sound since u8 has alignment 1 and size_of::<u8>() == 1;
  (c) `copy_nonoverlapping` in write_uint/write_uint128 (lib.rs:2001/2015/
  2187/2197) bounded by `assert!(nbytes <= buf.len())` and `nbytes <= 8/16`
  guards immediately preceding. Per the rubric these missing SAFETY comments
  cap the rating at `neutral`.
  
  Concern #3 (unsafe w/o miri): CI runs `cargo miri test --verbose` against
  the full test suite (.github/workflows/ci.yml:158-170) on nightly. The
  unsafe is pure-Rust (no FFI/syscalls) and miri-testable. No penalty.
  
  Concern #4 (correctness): no bugs identified. write_uint/write_uint128 use
  pack_size guards before slicing the BE byte buffer; signed n-byte helpers
  round-trip via extend_sign/unextend_sign. read_slice!/write_slice! macros
  use chunks_exact and a length assert. Float reads use f{32,64}::from_bits
  (no sNaN UB).
