comment: |-
  Minimal `no_std` I/O trait crate: two traits (`Read`, `Write`) plus a handful
  of blanket and concrete impls. The published tarball contains only
  Cargo.toml, README, LICENSE, .cargo_vcs_info.json, and src/lib.rs (265
  lines, including tests). No build.rs, no proc-macros, no dependencies, no
  features beyond `alloc`/`std`.
  
  Concern #1 (malicious/suspicious): none. Grep for `unsafe`, `include_bytes!`,
  `Command`, `libc`, `extern "C"`, `asm!`, `transmute`, `#[no_mangle]` returned
  zero matches. No I/O outside the documented trait surface. License
  (Apache-2.0) and repository link present and consistent with the parent
  `enarx/ciborium` project.
  
  Concern #2/#3 (`unsafe`): not applicable — no unsafe code, so SAFETY-comment
  and miri caps do not apply.
  
  Concern #4 (correctness): read every impl in lib.rs.
  - `Read for &[u8]` (lib.rs:108-122): `data.len() > self.len()` returns
    `EndOfFile`; otherwise `split_at(data.len())` + `copy_from_slice` is safe
    because the length check rules out the panic case.
  - `Write for &mut [u8]` (lib.rs:130-149): same bounds-check shape with
    `OutOfSpace`; uses `core::mem::take` to swap the slice out before
    `split_at_mut` to satisfy the borrow checker. Correct.
  - `Write for Vec<u8>`: `extend_from_slice`, `Infallible`. Correct.
  - Std blanket impls forward directly to `std::io::{Read,Write}`.
  - `&mut R` / `&mut W` forwarders for no_std mirror the std blanket impls.
  No off-by-ones, no overflow surface (no arithmetic on lengths), no panics
  reachable from documented inputs.
